CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 12, 1953, pg. 20 reads: "NAACP Youth Leaders- Mrs. Marian B. Jordon, left, Pittsburgh branch executive secretary, installed the NAACP Youth Council officers for 1954 last Sunday at the Centre Avenue YMCA. Those taking office included, left to right, the Misses Geraldine Wright, secretary; Lorraine Thorne, president, and Eloise Patterson, assistant recording secretary.  in rear are Frank Smith, treasurer; James Frazier, vice president, and George Nixon, assistant corresponding secretary. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Marian B. Jordon installing NAACP Youth Council officers for 1954, front row: Geraldine Wright, Lorraine Thorne, and Eloise Patterson; back row: Frank Smith, James Frazier, and George Nixon, standing in Centre Avenue YMCA, another version
